ational effects; (ii) affirm the thin (rms $7-23$\nkpc) planar \"arc\" of satellites that comprises roughly half (15) of the\ngalaxies within 300 kpc from M31; (iii) reassess physical proximity of notable\nassociations such as the NGC 147/185 pair and M33/AND XXII; and (iv) illustrate\nchallenges in tip-of-the-red-giant branch distances for galaxies with $M_V >\n-9.5$, which can be biased by up to 35%. We emphasize the importance of RR\nLyrae for accurate distances to faint galaxies that should be discovered by\nupcoming facilities (e.g., Rubin Observatory). We provide updated luminosities\nand sizes for our sample. Our distances will serve as the basis for future\ninvestigation of the star formation and orbital histories of the entire known\nM31 satellite system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jun 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Sep 2022 20:38:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
