ies. The ILT simultaneously allowed us to probe the nucleus\nat a resolution of $\\sim$0.3 arcsec, where we detected three components, and,\nfor the first time, diffuse emission around these components. Combining this\nwith archival high frequency VLA images of the nucleus allowed us to detect\nabsorption in one component, and a steep spectrum radio AGN in another. We then\nextrapolate from this case study to the importance of investigating the\npresence of radio emission in more ULIRGs and what it can tell us about the\nlink between mergers and the presence of radio activity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Jun 2022 18:42:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-03"}
