ich\nare kinases that play key roles in cell differentiation and programmed death.\nOne such kinase is RIPK1 that directly interacts with viral protein nsp12, the\nRdRp of the virus. The study produced many control hubs that were not targets\nof existing drugs but were enriched with proteins on membranes and the\nNF-$\\kappa$B pathway, so are excellent candidate targets for new drugs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jun 2022 02:17:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Jun 2023 12:18:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-02"}
